= Projects and Roadmaps =

== Core Flow ==
# Select template context (plant/category/product/roadmap)
# Register project
# Snapshot template roadmap structures into project tables
# Execute milestones, activities, and tasks
# Track status, comments, forms, attachments, and notifications

== Snapshotting Model ==
When a project is created, roadmap templates are materialized into project-owned tables.

This enables:
* immutable-at-time-of-registration structure
* project-specific changes without mutating source templates
* historical reproducibility and auditability

== Milestone Insertion Rules ==
Inserted project milestone roots are identified by a prefixed roadmap identifier rule:
* inserted roots use a prefix form (for example '''INS-...''')
* template descendants keep source roadmap identifiers

Behavioral implications:
* delete/move eligibility should be based on inserted-root logic
* compatibility fallback should allow deletion of legacy inserted roots based on parent/source roadmap mismatch

== Multi-Select Template Insert ==
Project milestone insertion from templates supports multiple selected milestone IDs in one action.

Service behavior collapses descendant selections under selected ancestors to prevent duplicate subtree insertion.

== Configure Sync Rule ==
Project configure operations that retrieve latest roadmap structure must compare roadmap IDs and prerequisite keys case-insensitively to avoid false deltas caused by GUID casing differences.

== Key Data Families ==
* Template side: ROADMAPS / ROADMAPMILESTONES / ROADMAPACTIVITIES / prerequisites
* Project side: PROJECTROADMAPS / PROJECTROADMAPMILESTONES / PROJECTROADMAPACTIVITIES / prereqs
* Execution side: PROJECTMILESTONES / PROJECTTASKS / status changes / comments / forms / attachments

